# Eclipse Theia Platform Overview

An open, flexible and extensible platform designed to efficiently develop and deliver cloud and desktop IDEs and tools using modern web technologies. The platform includes native support for AI-powered tools through Theia AI, with Theia IDE serving as a standard reference implementation.

## Core Platform Features

### Cloud & Desktop

With Theia you can develop one IDE and run it in a browser or as a native desktop application from a single source.

### Extensible

Theia is designed in a modular way to allow extenders and adopters to customize and extend every aspect.

The platform enables building fully customized or white-labeled products beyond standard extensions.

### Vendor Neutral

Theia is truly vendor-neutral and developed by a diverse community.

Hosted at an Open-Source Foundation rather than controlled by a single vendor. Multiple companies offer professional support.

### Modern Tech

Built on contemporary web technology stack featuring:

- Language support via LSP (Language Server Protocol)
- DAP (Debug Adapter Protocol) support
- VS Code extension hosting
- Full terminal access

**Note:** While it reuses components from VS Code, such as the Monaco editor, Theia is an independent platform with a modular architecture - NOT a fork of VS Code.

